doctype html
html
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0')
    title #{title} - Timestamp Microservice
    link(id='favicon', rel='icon', type='image/x-icon', href='')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Titillium+Web:300|700', rel='stylesheet')
    link(href='/style.css', rel='stylesheet')
    script(src='/script.js') 

  body
    header(class='head')
      h1(class='header') Timestamp Microservice
      h2(class='subhead') FreeCodeCamp Back End Certification API project #1
      
    main(class='container')
      div(class='row')
        div(class='card')
          h3(class='card__title') User stories:
          ul
            li I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
            li If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
            li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      div(class='row')
        div(class='col col-1')
          div(class='card')
            h3(class='card__title') Example Usage
            div(id='natural-link' class='card__url')
            div(id='unix-link' class='card__url')
            div(id='today' class='card__url')
        div(class='col col-2')
          div(class='card')
            h3(class='card__title') Example Output
            pre { unix: 1450117800, natural: "December 15, 2015" }
            
    footer(class='foot')
      div(class='icon__wrap')
        a(class='github' href='https://github.com/rifkegribenes/timestamp-ms')
          img(class='github' src='https://image.flaticon.com/icons/svg/25/25231.svg' alt='view code on github')